blog.name: couchsurfing
blog.description: Couch Stories is a collection of amazing and inspiring stories we find right here in the Couchsurfing community.

posts.caption: “I am in love with the mystery that is traveling, and the brilliance that is couch surfing.” ~ Keiko, describing her Couchsurfing adventures in the western United States, on her blog: http://bit.ly/1pEOlmP

What has changed for you through travel?

Traveler Angie Castells describes some of the incredible ways her life has changed forever after living abroad: http://bit.ly/1mFFWPX

"If you’re ever stranded in a small town because your road trip van maybe died, do not fret. Because there’s a possibility you could couchsurf with the sweetest, coolest, punk rock vegan couple that ever lived. And they will let you sleep in their teepee and then give you a beautiful pair of handmade wings to fly around life with (in case your van is doomed)! Ps I have always ALWAYS wanted costume wings so this was probably one of the best days of my life.”

~ @stephaniehurtado (http://bit.ly/1uIzEUV)

"Couchsurfing entered my life and brought a ton of amazing people and new good friends. I’ve been organizing the weekly vegan dinners for couchsurfers for a year now, and a couple of picnics off the beaten path I’m really grateful for all the cool people I’ve met this last year through CS."

~ Heart of a Vagabond - A vegan travel guide
The Couchsurfing community in Casablanca gathers for a massive outdoor meal. We love the custom logo that they added to the photo, too!
Are you a highly effective Couchsurfer? What habits would you add to this list of how to become a better traveler on Couchsurfing? http://bit.ly/UgqIFF
Stewie and Gabe work well together in a meeting at Couchsurfing headquarters!
Why should you go backpacking solo? Couchsurfer Ahmed cites Couchsurfing as one of his top 7 reasons! http://bit.ly/1jZyGty

On Friday nights, the Lima Couchsurfing Community comes together for Lima Babel, a ”live cultural exchange where friendships are made and everyone shares an unforgettable experience” ~Claudia

World traveler Claudia hosts Lima Babel “to make the Couchsurfing experience livelier and deeper, following the principles in which Couchsurfing is founded.”

To all Couchsurfers in Peru, “if you are in town, please stop by”.

Read about the Couchsurfing Core Principles here!

We had such a fantastic time celebrating International Couchsurfing Day with all of you last week!
Find highlights and our most hilarious photo booth moments here: http://bit.ly/SWOmpI !

After compiling our shared staff bucket list, three Couchsurfing team members decided to fulfill the top item on the list! They enjoyed a gorgeous morning in Napa, California, from the comfort of a hot air balloon. They would also love to say another huge thank you to their fantastic host Greg for putting them up on his couch!
Couchsurfers from all over East Java, Indonesia gathered to celebrate International Couchsurfing Day (June 12) together!

Happy International Couchsurfing Day 2014!

Our amazing Community in Yogyakarta, Indonesia - including their lizard (!) - celebrated Couchsurfing’s 15th birthday on June 12 with a lovingly prepared cake!
What items do you have on your bucket list?
What speechless moment has since become your go-to travel tale?

"Thanks for organizing such a fun, uplifting, rejuvenating and fun weekend, y’all. My faith in humanity is restored and my friend list is swollen with awesomeness. We look forward to having the southeast come crash the mountains sooner than later!"

- Couchsurfer attending the Charleston BeachCrash 2014
What have you learned by staying curious on your Couchsurfing adventures?

"I am now a couchsurfing host myself and have hosted people from all over the world. Without exception these travellers have been inspirational, and all have fascinating stories to tell." -Ian
